# Line endings, settled once and for all.
#
# THE PROBLEM THIS FIXES: this repo is edited from Windows AND from WSL. Windows
# git has core.autocrlf=true, WSL git does not. So the two disagreed about every
# text file in the repo: Windows git saw a clean tree, while WSL git reported
# ~191 files as "modified" — all of them byte-identical apart from CRLF vs LF.
# Committing that noise would have produced a 191-file diff containing zero real
# changes, and a commit made from inside WSL would have done exactly that.
#
# `text=auto eol=lf` overrides core.autocrlf in BOTH environments: LF in the
# repository, LF in the working tree, everywhere. One source of truth.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries must never be touched — normalizing these corrupts them.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.webp  binary
*.mp4   binary
*.webm  binary
*.pdf   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.eot   binary

# SVG is text (it's XML) and diffs usefully, so it is deliberately NOT binary.
